<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  launchd user agent for `warden-gated` (issue #3, ADR-0002/ADR-0006).

  Install:
    cp com.warden.gated.plist ~/Library/LaunchAgents/
    launchctl bootstrap gui/$(id -u) ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.warden.gated.plist
    launchctl enable gui/$(id -u)/com.warden.gated

  RunAtLoad + KeepAlive make this agent come back both after a machine
  restart and after a crash (acceptance criterion 2, issue #3: "warden-gated
  survit à un redémarrage machine"). Replace `HOME_PLACEHOLDER` below with
  the absolute home directory of the user this agent runs as (launchd does
  not expand `~` in plist values).

  Credentials for the real `origin` remote must already be usable by this
  process at start time (e.g. a running `ssh-agent`/keychain-backed SSH key,
  or a git credential helper configured on the `origin` remote inside the
  bare gate repo) -- nothing here embeds a secret directly.

  SECURITY NOTE (issue #3 review, ADR-0006 "Precision v1"): as written,
  this agent runs under `gui/$(id -u)` for whichever user installs it --
  the SAME OS user that (presumably) also runs `warden`. That gives a
  process/logical security boundary (no shared credential-access code,
  independent SQLite re-verification) but NOT OS-level isolation -- a
  `warden` compromised at the code level, running under this same UID, can
  read whatever this UID can read, including the SSH key / credential
  helper this agent relies on. For a boundary that holds even against a
  fully code-compromised `warden`, install and run this agent under a
  DEDICATED OS user (distinct from `warden`'s), owning the bare repo and
  the `origin` credentials exclusively -- see README.md, "Deploiement
  durci (isolation OS reelle)". This file intentionally keeps the simple
  same-user setup as its default for ease of installation.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
  <dict>
    <key>Label</key>
    <string>com.warden.gated</string>

    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array>
      <string>HOME_PLACEHOLDER/.cargo/bin/warden-gated</string>
      <string>serve</string>
      <string>--socket</string>
      <string>HOME_PLACEHOLDER/.warden/gated.sock</string>
      <string>--db</string>
      <string>HOME_PLACEHOLDER/.warden/state.db</string>
      <string>--bare-repo</string>
      <string>HOME_PLACEHOLDER/.warden/gate.git</string>
      <string>--branch</string>
      <string>main</string>
    </array>

    <key>RunAtLoad</key>
    <true/>
    <key>KeepAlive</key>
    <dict>
      <key>SuccessfulExit</key>
      <false/>
    </dict>

    <key>StandardOutPath</key>
    <string>HOME_PLACEHOLDER/.warden/warden-gated.log</string>
    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
    <string>HOME_PLACEHOLDER/.warden/warden-gated.err.log</string>
  </dict>
</plist>
